File: COVID-19 test. AFP/Jens Schlueter JOHANNESBURG - Deaths due to the novel coronavirus have surpassed 30,000. The health department recorded 434 cases in the last 24 hours. READ: Africa confronts second COVID-19 wave The death toll now stands at 30,011 after 434 more people died of COVID-19. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases is 1,113,349. Recoveries now stand at 911,573 which translates to a recovery rate of 90 percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs Open configuration options